{"id":1,"date":"2018-07-16T12:33:44","date_gmt":"2018-07-16T12:33:44","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/m-nex.net\/site?p=1"},"modified":"2018-08-04T11:52:35","modified_gmt":"2018-08-04T02:52:35","slug":"hello-world","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/m-nex.net\/ja\/hello-world\/","title":{"rendered":"M-Nex Kick-off Meeting in Sydney"},"content":{"rendered":"<div id=\"dslc-theme-content\"><div id=\"dslc-theme-content-inner\"><p>The delegates of M-Nex from 6 countries representing seven partners and one collaborator have collected in Sydney from May 16 to 18 for the kick-off meeting of the M-Nex Project. We visited Architectural design companies, exchanged information on latest design projects in Australia and Asian-Pacific countries. Project members shared the preparation work on starting up M-Nex in each country and discussed working plan as a whole and also by work package. On the final day, the participants visited the water treatment in the Central Park of Sydney, learnt the advanced project in the world, in nexus of water, energy and green.<\/p>\n<p>Participants:<\/p>\n<p><em>Keio University, Japan<\/em><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li><em>Professor Wanglin Yan<\/em><\/li>\n<li><em>Professor Rajib Shaw<\/em><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><em>Qartar University, Qatar<\/em><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li><em>Dr, Anna Grichting, Assistant Professor, Qatar\u00a0University<\/em><\/li>\n<li><em>Ms. <\/em>Maryam, Master\u2019s student<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><em>University of Michigan, USA<\/em><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li><em>Dr. Geoffrey Th\u00fcn, Associate Professor<\/em><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><em>Delft University of Technology, The Netherlands<\/em><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li><em>Professor Andy van den\u00a0Dobbelsteen<\/em><\/li>\n<li><em>Mr. Nick<\/em><em>ten Caat, PhD student<\/em><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><em>Queens\u00a0University\u00a0Belfast<\/em><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li><em>Professor Greg Keeffe<\/em><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><em>Institute for Global Environmental Strategies,<\/em><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li><em>Dr. Bijon Kumer\u00a0Mitra, Senior Policy Researcher<\/em><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><em>Maccreanor Lavington, UK<\/em><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li><em>Mr. Kevin Logan,\u00a0Associate Director<\/em><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><em>University of Technology Sydney, Australia<\/em><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li><em>Professor Rob Roggema<\/em><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-23\" src=\"http:\/\/m-nex.net\/site\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/07\/UNADJUSTEDNONRAW_thumb_169db-1024x677.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1024\" height=\"677\" srcset=\"https:\/\/m-nex.net\/site\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/07\/UNADJUSTEDNONRAW_thumb_169db-1024x677.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/m-nex.net\/site\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/07\/UNADJUSTEDNONRAW_thumb_169db-1024x677-300x198.jpg 300w, https:\/\/m-nex.net\/site\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/07\/UNADJUSTEDNONRAW_thumb_169db-1024x677-768x508.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" \/><\/p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-33\" src=\"http:\/\/m-nex.net\/site\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/07\/UNADJUSTEDNONRAW_thumb_168cf-1024x768.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1024\" height=\"768\" srcset=\"https:\/\/m-nex.net\/site\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/07\/UNADJUSTEDNONRAW_thumb_168cf-1024x768.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/m-nex.net\/site\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/07\/UNADJUSTEDNONRAW_thumb_168cf-1024x768-300x225.jpg 300w, https:\/\/m-nex.net\/site\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/07\/UNADJUSTEDNONRAW_thumb_168cf-1024x768-768x576.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" \/><\/p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-32\" src=\"http:\/\/m-nex.net\/site\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/07\/UNADJUSTEDNONRAW_thumb_1689f-1024x768.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1024\" height=\"768\" srcset=\"https:\/\/m-nex.net\/site\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/07\/UNADJUSTEDNONRAW_thumb_1689f-1024x768.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/m-nex.net\/site\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/07\/UNADJUSTEDNONRAW_thumb_1689f-1